text: The 1995 Russian Figure Skating Championships () took place in Moscow. Skaters competed in the disciplines of men's singles, ladies' singles, pair skating, and ice dancing. The results were one of the criteria used to pick the Russian teams to the 1995 World Championships and the 1995 European Championships. ==Senior results== ===Men=== {| class="wikitable" |- ! Rank !
